==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrimshaw
<hw>Scrim"shaw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To ornament, as
shells, ivory, etc., by engraving, and (usually) rubbing pigments into
the incised lines.</def> <mark>[Sailor's cant. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrimshaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scrimshaw
<hw>Scrim"shaw`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shell, a whale's tooth, or
the like, that is scrimshawed.</def> <mark>[Sailor's cant,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrine</ent>⟦br⟧
